<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-1657] Make &quot;boolean readOnly&quot; a required arg to IndexReader.open</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1657</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;Most apps don&apos;t need read/write IndexReader, and, a readOnly&lt;br/&gt;
IndexReader has better concurrent performance.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d love to simply default readOnly to true, and you&apos;d have to specify&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;false&quot; if you want a read/write reader (I think that&apos;s the natural&lt;br/&gt;
default), but I think that&apos;d break too many back-compat cases.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So the workaround is to make the parameter explicit, in 2.9.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think even for IndexSearcher&apos;s methods that open an IndexReader&lt;br/&gt;
under the hood, we should also make the parameter explicit.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
